The portion in which we are chiefly interested consists of 43 folios, on the last of which the writing hardly extends to one column. Every page except the last has two columns, neatly written, with initial letters and rubrics, each column having 41 lines, and the - whole page measuring 275 x 190 millimetres.

I am supported by the very valuable opinion of Dr. Warner or the British Museum in asserting that this MS, like that at Barcelona, must have been written at a date not far removed from that of the death of St. Francis in 1226, and certainly not later than the first half of the 13th century.
